{"title":"Petrifying Cloud","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Petrifying_Cloud","type":"markdown","data":"***Version [0.30](/0.30 \"0.30\")**: This article **may not be** up to date for the [latest stable release](/0.32 \"0.32\") of Crawl.*\n\n|   |                                                                                          |\n| - | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|   | Exhales calcifying dust, which petrifies anyone affected for longer than a brief moment. |\n\n**Petrifying Cloud** is a monster-only spell which emits a stream of [clouds](/Cloud \"Cloud\") of calcifying dust, dealing minor damage on impact. Anything that ends its turn inside a cloud has a chance to start [petrifying](/Petrify \"Petrify\"). The higher your [XL](/XL \"XL\") ([HD](/HD \"HD\") for monsters), the less likely for the petrification attempt is to be successful.\n\nFor players, those who are a [Gargoyle](/Gargoyle \"Gargoyle\"), in certain forms ([Statue Form](/Statue_Form \"Statue Form\"), [Shadow Form](/Shadow_Form \"Shadow Form\"), [Storm Form](/Storm_Form \"Storm Form\"), [Wisp Form](/Wisp_Form \"Wisp Form\")), or under [Zin](/Zin \"Zin\")'s Vitalisation are immune to petrification, while [Qazlal](/Qazlal \"Qazlal\") makes you immune to all clouds. You'll still take impact damage, though. For monsters, [gargoyles](/List_of_gargoyles \"List of gargoyles\"), [statues](/Statue \"Statue\"), [insubstantial](/Insubstantial \"Insubstantial\") monsters, [earth elementals](/Earth_elemental \"Earth elemental\"), and [catoblepae](/Catoblepae \"Catoblepae\") themselves are similarly immune.\n\nThe following enemies cast Petrifying Cloud:\n\n- Y [![Catoblepas.png](/images/3/3b/Catoblepas.png)](/File:Catoblepas.png) **[Catoblepas](/Catoblepas \"Catoblepas\")** (2d6 damage)\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Petrifying Cloud - CrawlWiki</titl